ZH: 我的下属昨天提交了一个重要的报告。
EN: My subordinate submitted an important report yesterday.

ZH: 经理给下属安排了一个新的项目。
EN: The manager assigned a new project to the subordinate.

ZH: 下属们非常尊重他们的上司。
EN: The subordinates have a great respect for their boss.

ZH: 我下属的工作表现一直都非常出色。
EN: The work performance of my subordinates has always been outstanding.

ZH: 这位领导非常关心他的下属的福利。
EN: This leader is very concerned about the welfare of his subordinates.

ZH: 我和我的下属之间有很好的合作关系。
EN: I have a great working relationship with my subordinates.

ZH: 上级应该指导和支持他们的下属。
EN: Superiors should guide and support their subordinates.

ZH: 我的下属们为实现目标而努力工作。
EN: My subordinates work hard to achieve the goals.

ZH: 这位领导对下属的发展非常重视。
EN: This leader values the development of the subordinates greatly.

ZH: 下属们每天都会向我汇报工作进展。
EN: The subordinates report their work progress to me every day.

ZH: 他的下属们都很喜欢他，因为他给他们提供了良好的工作环境。
EN: His subordinates all like him because he provides them with a good working environment.

ZH: 领导需要鼓励和激励下属。
EN: Leaders need to encourage and motivate their subordinates.

ZH: 我的下属们每天都准时上班。
EN: My subordinates come to work on time every day.

ZH: 领导应该给予下属足够的自主权。
EN: Leaders should give their subordinates enough autonomy.

ZH: 那个经理对他下属的要求很高。
EN: That manager has high expectations for his subordinates.

ZH: 下属的培训对于他们的职业发展非常重要。
EN: The training of the subordinates is crucial for their professional development.

ZH: 领导和下属之间要保持良好的沟通。
EN: Good communication should be maintained between leaders and subordinates.

ZH: 下属们通过努力工作赢得了领导的赞扬。
EN: The subordinates won the praise from the leader through their hard work.

ZH: 领导的指导对下属的成长很有帮助。
EN: The leader's guidance is very helpful for the growth of the subordinates.

ZH: 他非常尊重他的下属的意见和建议。
EN: He respects the opinions and suggestions of his subordinates greatly.
